quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  25,1,"Supremely Blessed be the One Who bestowed the Criterion from on high upon His servant, to be a warner{1}to all realms.",1:[The Arabic text can imply either the Prophet (peace be upon him) as a warner, or the Criterion as a warning.]
  25,2,"The One to Whom belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth, and Who has not taken for Himself any offspring nor has He any associate in the dominion, and He has created everything and determined its measure."
